      <section id="why">
        <h2>ü§î Why?</h2>
        <p>I wanted something that would help keep track of online reading without it becoming another inbox. RSS readers can be overwhelming, but it's nice to know when there's something new.</p>
        <p>I also wanted to go back to reading blogs <em>in situ</em>, rather than stripped of context in a reader.<p>
      </section>

      <section id="man">
        <h2>üìí Manual</h2>
        <p>It's a pretty simple tool but it still helps to read the manual.</p>

        <h3 id="man-unread">Unread count</h3>
        <p>When you <button class="add">Add</button> a link, the app will try and fetch RSS data for that site.<p>
        <ul>
          <li>If an RSS feed is found, an unread count is displayed next to the link</li>
          <li>When you click the link, the count resets. If the count is zero, it's hidden</li>
          <li>The app will routinely check RSS feeds for updates in the background</li>
          <li>If no RSS feed is found, a "?" will be displayed where the count would be</li>
          <li>You can hide the count for any link in <em>Edit mode</em></li>
        </ul>

        <h3 id="man-order">Link order</h3>
        <p>Links are ordered based on when you last clicked on them, with most recent clicks on the bottom.<p>

        <h3 id="man-editing">Edit mode</h3>
        <p>Click on the <button class="edit">Edit</button> to enter <em>Edit mode</em>. Here you can:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Change the title of your home page</li>
          <li>Change the CSS styles for your home page</li>
          <li>Import/export links as <code>.opml</code> files</li>
          <li>Edit links:
          <ul>
            <li>Update the link name</li>
            <li>Update the main link address</li>
            <li>Update the RSS feed address</li>
            <li>Set whether the unread count displays for that link</li>
          </ul>
          </li>
          <li>Delete links</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Then click <button class="submit">Done</button> to go back to the normal view.</p>
      </section>

